description: Team India openers, Jaiswal and Rohit, were on opposing sides in Jaipur, yet their camaraderie shone through, with Jaiswal's admiration for his senior clearly apparent. In a video on 'X', Jaiswal, who shares the opening partnership with Rohit in international cricket, was captured approaching his national team captain and embracing him warmly after Rajasthan Royals beat Mumbai Indians.
title: Watch: 'Jaiswal aur uske Rohit bhaiya' - India's jodi No. 1

description: The navy reported that a tragic incident took place during a rehearsal for their upcoming 90th anniversary celebration at a naval base located in northern Perak state. The accident involved two helicopters, resulting in the loss of all crew members on board. "All victims were confirmed dead on site," the navy stated in a concise statement, mentioning that the remains of the deceased have been transported to the hospital for identification purposes.
title: 10 dead after Malaysian Navy helicopters collide mid-air

description: M Krishnan, a 40-year-old Indian-origin married man, was sentenced to 20 years in jail on Monday for culpable homicide not amounting to murder of his girlfriend, Mallika Begum Rahamansa Abdul Rahman, 40.  In 2015, Krishnan started an extramarital affair with Mallika, who had two daughters from her previous marriages, Singapore law watch reported.
title: Married Indian-origin man jailed in Singapore for killing gf

description: The saffron landscape of Gujarat witnesses community protests for the first time in Lok Sabha polls, where Kshatriyas voice against BJP's Rajkot candidate, impacting caste dynamics and past Patidar movements, adding complexity to the electoral narrative.
title: What’s cooking in Gujarat’s caste cauldron?

description: Nasa granted awards for the human exploration rover challenge on Monday to two Indian student teams from Delhi-NCR and Mumbai. The "Crash and Burn" award went to the KIET Group of Institutions in Delhi-NCR, while the "Rookie of the Year" went to Kanakia International School in Mumbai. The annual engineering competition concluded on April 19 and 20.
title: Indian students bag Nasa awards for rover challenge

description: Yashasvi Jaiswal's unbeaten 104-run blitz against Mumbai Indians in IPL 2024 has etched his name in the tournament's history. The 22-year-old's blistering innings, his second IPL century, joins an elite group who've achieved the feat against a single team. Jaiswal's display of batting prowess, with 9 fours and 7 sixes, highlights his rapid scoring ability and solid technique.
title: Jaiswal joins Kohli, Gayle in an elite list after his knock vs MI

description: Soma Das, a cancer survivor, is the sole candidate unaffected by Calcutta High Court's termination of SSC's 2016 selection process. She advocates for reappointing genuine candidates based on merit.
title: Kolkata teacher exempt from mass termination unsure how to react

description: Delhi CM Kejriwal received insulin in Tihar jail for high sugar level. AAP praised BJP while Kejriwal credited Lord Hanuman. Court denied his plea for daily consultations. Enforcement Directorate was involved in the arrest related to money laundering probe.
title: Delhi CM Kejriwal administered insulin for first time in Tihar jail
Ex-Mumbai top cop & BJD Puri LS nominee faints due to heat
Man with 26/11 link held for recce of Banerjee's house, office

description: Former Punjab Congress president Kaypee switched to Shiromani Akali Dal. Chaudhary criticized Channi's impact on Jalandhar Congress. Urgency for high command intervention due to defections.
title: Punjab Cong ex-chief Kaypee joins SAD, to fight from Jalandhar

description: Police investigate FIRs against social media promoting AI-generated deepfake videos of actors Ranveer Singh & Aamir Khan. Singh warns on X, files complaint. Khan's clip also went viral.
title: Ranveer Singh deepfake video viral, FIR against handle

description: Rajasthan Royals' leg-spinner Yuzvendra Chahal became the first bowler to reach 200 IPL wickets, achieving the milestone in his 153rd match, which was against Mumbai Indians in Jaipur. He currently shares the top wicket-taker position in the ongoing season as well with Jasprit Bumrah and Harshal Patel. All three have 13 wickets each.
title: Watch: Mishra's cheeky message to Chahal for 200 IPL wickets

description: Elon Musk said Tuesday his social media platform X will appeal against an Australian injunction forcing it to take down videos of a church stabbing in Sydney. Australia's internet watchdog secured an injunction late Monday, forcing X to hide videos that allegedly show a Sydney bishop being slashed in the head during a live-streamed sermon. X ignored earlier Australian pleas to remove the images, and Musk had said the company would appeal against the injunction on free speech grounds.
title: Elon Musk, Australian PM clash over church stabbing posts

description: Calcutta HC invalidated 25,758 SSC appointments, except Soma Das, ordering 1,600 recruits to return salaries. CBI to probe 'cash-for-jobs' case. Mamata Banerjee criticizes HC's order and alleges selective verdicts.
title: Mamata's next step? 25,757 from 2016 appointments to lose jobs

description: KL Rahul, a top contender for the Indian cricket squad's T20 World Cup spot, has returned to form with an 82-run knock against Chennai Super Kings in the IPL on Friday. Lucknow Super Giants captain is expected to replicate his performance against the same opponent on Tuesday at MA Chidambaram Stadium.
title: IPL: Chennai out to get Rahul early and stop Lucknow

description: Columbia canceled in-person classes, dozens of protesters were arrested at New York University and Yale, and the gates to Harvard Yard were closed to the public on Monday as some of the most prestigious U.S. universities sought to defuse campus tensions over Israel's war with Hamas. Columbia President Minouche Shafik said in a message to the school community Monday that she was “deeply saddened” by what was happening on campus.
title: Tensions flare at US universities over pro-Palestinian protests

description: UK relocates asylum seekers to Rwanda to deter irregular migration, facing legal challenges. Safety of Rwanda Bill passed to affirm UK sovereignty. Potential hurdles from European Court of Human Rights commitments and ongoing legal delays.
title: UK passes Sunak's ambitious Rwanda migrant bill after 2 years

description: Mumbai crime branch finds pistol from Tapi river linked to Salman Khan's home shooting. Shooters Gupta & Pal threw guns. Gangster Bishnoi allegedly ordered the act. Pal seeks gang notoriety. Police pursue Bishnoi's custody and lookout for brother.
title: Salman Khan home firing: 1 gun found in Gujarat river

description: Aam Aadmi Party accuses Tihar Jail superintendent of false health statements about Kejriwal. Kejriwal demanded insulin, showed high sugar levels to AIIMS doctors, arrested for money laundering.
title: Arvind Kejriwal pained to read 'false' statements: AAP

description: WeWork Inc. plans Indian market exit, sells 27% stake. Embassy Group's joint venture ownership reduces. Enam group, A91 Partners, Mithun Sacheti to acquire stake. Post-pandemic, demand for co-working spaces rises in India.
title: WeWork is exiting India market, to sell entire stake in the country

description: Ola launched cab operations at Maharishi Valmiki International Airport in Ayodhya, with a dedicated pickup zone and round-the-clock assistance for travelers. Bhavish Aggarwal aims to unlock growth opportunities and increase revenue.
title: Ola first app-based cab company to launch services at Ayodhya airport

description: Harbhajan Singh endorses Sanju Samson as India's wicketkeeper-batsman for the T20 World Cup, highlighting his consistent performance and advocating for a leadership role for him in T20Is, contrasting with other contenders like Rishabh Pant, KL Rahul and Ishan Kishan. T20 World Cup runs from June 2 to 29 in the USA and Canada.
title: Harbhajan says this player should be India's wicketkeeper in T20 WC

description: Kartik Bakale, son of Gadag-Betgeri City Municipal Council vice-president Sunanda Bakale and Prakash Bakale, and three members of the Hadimani family visiting the Bakales were hacked to death around 2.30am Friday after assailants gained entry by breaking open the first-floor windows of the room in which the Hadimanis were sleeping.
title: Son gave supari to kill parents, bro; hitmen killed 3 guests instead in Karnataka's Gadag

description: Sanjeev Balyan faces challenges in Muzaffarnagar due to Hindu vote consolidation post-2013 riots. Rajput groups protest lack of representation, impacting Balyan's support. Sangeet Som's involvement stirs unrest against Balyan, adding complexity to the election dynamics.
title: In ‘refugee camps’ for over 10 yrs, voters vocal but see no hope
In ‘refugee camps’ for over 10 yrs, voters vocal but see no hope

description: In Kerala, political parties are fiercely competing for minority votes, focusing on countering the Sangh Parivar's 'communal fascist agenda'. In Malabar districts, not a single night has passed since the Centre notified the rules of Citizenship (Amendment) Act (CAA) on March 16 without political parties hitting the streets with flaming torches and chanting spirited anti-CAA slogans.
title: Lok Sabha elections: Why everyone’s chasing minority votes in Kerala
Why everyone’s chasing minority votes in Kerala

description: Indian students aiming for education abroad overwhelmingly favor the US, with a notable 69% majority expressing their desire to study there. Despite apprehensions regarding affordability, safety, and security, highlighted in the latest release of Oxford International's Student Global Mobility Index (SGMI), the US has outpaced other popular destinations like the UK (54%), Canada (43%), and Australia (27%).
title: US top choice for Indian students, followed by UK: Report

description: While the MI squad was on its way back to their hotel from the Sawai Mansingh Stadium in Jaipur following their loss to the Rajasthan Royals on Monday, their bus found itself amidst the bustling Jaipur traffic. This gave some fortunate fans the opportunity to get a close glimpse of India captain Rohit, who happened to be seated by a window.
title: Watch: 'Hamara captain kaisa ho...' - when MI bus got stuck

description: The opening statements on Monday in the first criminal trial of a former US president delineated a precise strategy by prosecutors to argue Donald Trump's alleged law-breaking, while also revealing the defense's multifaceted approach to contesting the charges.
title: Trump's hush-money trial: Key takeaways from opening statements

description: Following the victory of the pro-China ruling People's National Congress (PNC) in the parliamentary elections of the Maldives, Beijing expressed complete respect for the decision of the Maldivian people. China reiterated its commitment to enhancing the strategic partnership with the archipelago nation. President Mohamed Muizzu's party secured a super-majority in parliament with over 60 seats, which is interpreted as an affirmation of his foreign policy.
title: China hails Muizzu's win, eyes deeper ties
Startups raise $2 billion in Q4, 40% less than a year ago

description: Sagar shares how Instagram impacted his career, showcasing guitar skills, and refuting dating rumors with Nishi Saxena, emphasizing their friendship.
title: Sagar Parekh reveals, Avneet Kaur who encouraged him to make an insta account
